<TITLE> Green light for 10 new power plants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16 (bdnews24.com)-- The government has approved a project to build ten new power plants, planning minister AK Khandaker said on Tuesday. The Tk 7203 crore project will be implemented by the end of 2011, said Khandaker after an ECNEC meeting chaired by prime minister Sheikh Hasina. Ten diesel-fired or furnace fuel-fired peaking power plants of a total 830 megawatt capacity would be built under the project. "Peaking power plants are meant for generating electricity during the peak hours," the planning minister told a press briefing after the meeting of the Executive Committee of the National Economic Council (ECNEC). Of the Tk 7203 crore, the government will provide Tk 7085 crore and the rest will come from the Bangladesh Power Development Board (BPDB), he added. According to the project details, a 200-megawatt plant will would be built in Ghorashal of Narsingdi district and three 100-megawatt power plants in Haathhajari and Dohajari of Chittagong and in Gopalganj. An 80-megawatt plant will be installed in Bera of Pabna district and five 50-megawatt power plants in Baghabari of Pabna, Katakhali of Rajshahi, Shantahar of Naogaon, Daudkandi of Comilla and in Faridpur district. Tuesday's meeting has also approved a project to renovate the Ashuganj Power Plant Complex. The project, costing Tk 1025 crore, aims to modify and renovate the units 3, 4 and 5 of the Ashuganj Power Plant Complex, said Khandaker. "Of the Tk 1025 Crore, Tk 703 crore would come from government sources and Tk 322 from development partners." Meanwhile, the ECNEC also gave the green light to a Tk 597 crore project of the agriculture ministry for development and production of paddy, wheat and corn along with a Tk 781 crore project of the water resources ministry. Another Tk 106 crore has been approved for the second phase of the Comprehensive Village Development Project. ECNEC also gave nod to a Tk 4035 crore project for stipends at primary-level education and a Tk 75 crore project for constructing the Bangladesh Film Archive complex.
